  "Description": "COPYRIGHT 2009 BLUE CROSS/BLUE SHIELD OF KANSAS CITY \n\n\n\nMODIFICATIONS:\nDeveloper                          Date                 Project/Altiris #               Change Description                             Development Project      Code Reviewer            Date Reviewed\n----------------------------------      -------------------    -----------------------------------     ---------------------------------------------------------      ----------------------------------   ---------------------------------    -------------------------   \n\n\n  Razia                        10-19-2021           US-428909            Copied over from                                                  IntegrateDev1             Goutham K                  11/9/2021\n                                                                                                       CblTalnClmLnHlthCstGrpCntl to Load \n                                                                                                       the new Rpcl Table                      \n\n\nGoutham Kalidindi       1/25/2022          US-486153        Chanegd Extract file format to read Unix EOL          IntegrateDev2             Reddy Sanam                01/26/2022\n                                                                                                     Change from DOS and dedup data\n\nAnnotations:\nThe extracted records will be loaded into the global temp table #TempOwner#.BLUEKC_HCG_TEMP created during runtime.\n\nKey Columns for the temp table: CLM_ID, CLM_LN_SEQ_NO,SRC_SYS_CD\n\nThe GRANT access is given the development team to debug in case if there is any issues (abort).\n\nThis temp table will be deleted after the records are loaded into the table #$IDSOwner#.CLM_LN_HLTH_CST_GRP in the job CblTalnIdsClmLnHlthCstGrpLoad.\nJob name: CblTalnIdsClmLnHlthCstGrpRsltExtr\nINPUT : MILLIMAN.BLUEKC_HCG_OUTPUT.<YearMo>.TXT\nOUTPUT: #TempOwner#.BLUEKC_HCG_TEMP\n\nExtracts the records from the file and load into the global temporary table BLUEKC_HCG_TEMP."
